seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Introduction
body: Jodi Chapman shares her journey on becoming a naturopath and how her experiences and studies have led to her expertise in nutrition and mental distress.
teaser: Jodi Chapman shares her journey on becoming a naturopath and how her experiences and studies have led to her expertise in nutrition and mental distress.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 1. Removing The Irritants
body: In this FMTV exclusive Naturopath and nutritionist, Jodi Chapman discusses with James Colquhoun, step 1 to freeing yourself from your anxiety, depression and ADHD. In this the interview, you will learn how to control your mental state through identifying the irritants in your life that exacerbate your mood changes. In addition, you will gain a greater understanding of common foods that affect mood, learn to listen to your body's biofeedback and find out what you should get your practitioner to test you for.
teaser: Learn to identify the irritants in your life that exacerbate your anxiety, depression and ADHD with naturopath and nutritionist Jodi Chapman.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 2. Malabsorption & Gut Bacteria
body: In this interview, Jodi Chapman explores the relationship between gut health and mental distress. Jodi explains the scientific process of brain chemical synthesis in the gut and how our gut bacteria initiates the formation of proteins which make our mood hormones, dopamine, and serotonin. Along with the biochemical process of mood hormone creation, Jodi discusses the importance of certain strains of gut bacteria which we need to have present and how we can recolonize them in our digestive system. You will also learn about the benefits of fermented foods, how you can identify if your gut bacteria is out of whack and what you should be asking your health practitioner.
teaser: In this interview, Jodi Chapman explains the importance of gut health in relation to brain chemical synthesis and how their roles intertwine.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 3. Nutrient Deficiencies
body: In step 3 of controlling your anxiety, depression and ADHD Jodi Chapman explains the secondary result of step 2, malabsorption of nutrients in the gut resulting in the deficiency of essential vitamins and minerals, particularly the ones that build the pathways of your brain chemicals. In this presentation, Jodi discusses the key vitamins that contribute to brain function, how to identify which nutrients you are deficient in and whether supplementation is right for you.
teaser: Malabsorption of nutrients can result in deficiencies, understanding which vitamins and minerals your body may be lacking can affect the brain chemical function and ultimately your mood.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 4. Recovering Through Diet
body: After learning how your digestive system can become inflamed, resulting in malabsorption and deficiency of essential vitamins and nutrients, Jodi Chapman discusses with James Colquhoun how to nourish your body through diet. In this presentation you will learn about the scientific rationale behind macronutrients and their effect on your brain chemicals, how to pair foods for ultimate nutrient absorption and gain a greater understanding as to which foods may affect your mood.
teaser: After learning about the irritants and deficiencies that exacerbate moods, Jodi Chapman delves into the way you can nourish your body and aid these deficiencies through diet.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 5. The Cycle Of Stress
body: Step 5 for controlling your anxiety, depression and ADHD is to control, to reduce, and to manage stress. As explained by Jodi Chapman, stress can be a result or a precursor to the steps previously outlined in the presentation. Stress that is not managed can result in an imbalance of hormones, lack of homeostasis control, an increase in allergy irritation and even inflammation. You will learn about the cyclic effect of stress, malabsorption, deficiencies and mood, and how to identify when you are becoming stressed, how to manage and reciprocate to your body's biofeedback to heightening levels of stress.
teaser: Beyond nutrition, stress can become an integral factor playing a role in hormone balance and digestive health which can lead to an increase emotional distress.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 6. Understanding Your Hormones
body: Following on from step 5, step 6 focuses on the effect of hormones and how understanding them on a deeper level can help you take control of your emotional distress. In this presentation, you will learn the importance of your hormones and their role in the function of the body and how a multitude of external factors can interfere with their natural balance. Jodi Chapman also shares the key hormones which contribute to your mental state, how you can discover which hormones are causing you grief and ideas for lifestyle modifications that can assist in your re-balance.
teaser: Hormones are essential for regulating many functions of the body, however, many external factors can interfere with this, join Jodi Chapman as she explains, the role of hormones in the body and how they can give rise to emotional distress.

seriesTitle: Free Yourself From Anxiety, Depression and ADHD Interview With Jodi Chapman
title: Step 7. Understanding Developmental Brain Frequencies
body: The final step of freeing yourself from depression and anxiety, as explained by Jodi Chapman is a step that is not necessary for all people suffering from mental distress. Step 7 may not be present for someone who has taken control of the other actions outlined in the previous interviews. In this concluding step, Jodi discusses with James the notion of brain wave patterns and how these patterns can be learned or developed through growth, upbringing or personal experience. These particular frequencies of brain waves can cause irregular dopamine or serotonin production and ultimately lead to enhanced emotional distress. In this interview, you will learn about options for retraining motor neurone pathways and lifestyle modifications that can help support your recovery.
teaser: Step 7 of controlling your anxiety, depression and ADHD is understanding your brain wave patterns and retraining thought patterns using Neurotherapy and meditation techniques.
